<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1210,2027]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">The smooth-walled stomach is small and elongated transversely. It is completely covered by several branched hepatic lobes. The primary loop of the gut is widely open. The border of the anus is smooth. There is one gonad on each side. They consist of approximately 11 sac-like testicular follicles aligned on both sides of a central tubular ovary. The oocytes are big and spherical; almost the same size as each individual testicular sac. No endocarps are present.</paragraph>
