<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1210,2027]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1930,1955]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the deepest record of the species, increasing its bathymetric range in 
<specimenCount box="[1181,1259,1930,1955]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="generic">
<quantity box="[1181,1255,1930,1955]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="m" value="600.0">600 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
This is also the northernmost record of the species in the SW Atlantic Ocean, increasing its known range of distribution which also includes the South Western Pacific and Southern Indian Oceans.
</paragraph>
